{"title_page": "Harry Atwater", "text_new": "{{more footnotes|date=July 2012}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name = Harry Atwater\n| birth_name= Harry Albert Atwater, Jr.\n| alma_mater = [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]]\n| workplaces = [[California Institute of Technology]]\n| doctoral_students = [[Jennifer Dionne]]\n| fields            = {{plainlist|\n*[[Photonics]]\n*[[Metamaterial]]s\n*[[Surface plasmon|Plasmonics]]\n}}\n| thesis_title      = Ion beam enhanced grain growth in thin films\n| thesis_url        = https://dspace.mit.edu/handle/1721.1/49890\n| thesis_year       = 1987\n| doctoral_advisors  = {{plainlist|\n* Henry I. Smith\n* Carl V. Thompson\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Harry Albert Atwater, Jr.'''<ref>{{cite thesis |last=Atwater, Jr. |first=Harry Albert |date=1987 |title=Ion beam enhanced grain growth in thin films |type= PhD |chapter= |publisher=Massachusetts Institute of Technology |docket= |oclc= |url=https://dspace.mit.edu/handle/1721.1/49890 |access-date=}}</ref> is a Howard Hughes Professor and Professor of [[Applied Physics]] and [[Materials Science]] at the [[California Institute of Technology]]. Since 2014 he is the editor-in-chief of the journal [[ACS Photonics]], published by the [[American Chemical Society]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pubs.acs.org/page/apchd5/profile.html |title=Editor profile - ACS Photonics |accessdate=2014-08-20 }}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nAtwater received his S.B. (1981), S.M. (1983), and Ph.D. (1987) in [[electrical engineering]] from the [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]].  He serves as Director of the DOE Energy Frontier Research Center on Light-Material Interactions in Solar Energy Conversion and was named Director of the Resnick Institute for Science, Energy and Sustainability, Caltech\u2019s largest endowed research program focused on energy.  Atwater is founder and chief technical advisor for Alta Devices, a venture-backed company in Santa Clara, CA developing a transformational high efficiency/low cost photovoltaics technology, and Aonex Corporation, a compound semiconductor materials company.  He has also served an editorial board member for Surface Review and Letters.  Professor Atwater has actively served the materials community in various capacities, including [[Materials Research Society]] Meeting Chair (1997)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mrs.org/fall1997|title=1997 MRS Fall Meeting {{!}} Boston|website=www.mrs.org|access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref>, Materials Research Society President (2000)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mrs.org/past-mrs-presidents|title=Past MRS Presidents|website=www.mrs.org|access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref>, AVS Electronic Materials and Processing Division Chair (1999), and Board of Trustees of the Gordon Research Conferences.  In 2008, he served as Chair for the Gordon Research Conference on Plasmonics.\n\n==Research==\nHis research interests center around two interwoven research themes: [[photovoltaics]] and [[solar energy]]; and [[plasmon]]ics and optical [[metamaterials]].  Atwater and his group have been active in photovoltaics research for more than 20 years.  They have created new photovoltaic devices, including the silicon wire array solar cell, and layer-transferred fabrication approaches to III-V semiconductor III-V and [[Multijunction photovoltaic cell|multijunction cells]], as well as making advances in plasmonic light absorber structures for III-V compound and silicon thin films.  His research group\u2019s developments in the solar and plasmonics field have been featured in [[Scientific American]] and in research papers in [[Science (journal)|Science]], [[Nature Materials]], [[Nature Photonics]] and [[Advanced Materials]].\n\n== Awards ==\nAtwater is an MRS Fellow <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mrs.org/mrs-fellows-2011|title=2011 MRS Fellows|website=www.mrs.org|access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref>and has been honored by awards including the 2012 [[ENI award]] for Renewable and Non-Conventional Energy; MRS Kavli Lecturer in Nanoscience in 2010; Popular Mechanics Breakthrough Award, 2010; Joop Los Fellowship from the Dutch Society for Fundamental Research on Matter  in 2005,  A.T. & T. Foundation Award, 1990; NSF Presidential Young Investigator Award, 1989; IBM Faculty Development Award, 1989-1990; Member, Bohmische Physical Society, 1990; IBM Postdoctoral Fellowship, 1987. He is a member of the National Academy of Engineering.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://daedalus.caltech.edu/team-member/harry-atwater/|title=Professor Harry Atwater|website=Atwater Research Group|language=en|access-date=2019-12-29}}</ref> \n\n== Selected publications ==\n* {{cite journal|last1=Atwater|first1=Harry A.|last2=Polman|first2=Albert|title=Plasmonics for improved photovoltaic devices|journal=Nature Materials|volume=9|issue=3|year=2010|pages=205\u2013213|issn=1476-1122|doi=10.1038/nmat2629|pmid=20168344|bibcode=2010NatMa...9..205A|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/01b5d3ac672a11474e3a703119a1f80134b5017e}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Atwater|first1=Harry A.|title=The Promise of Plasmonics|journal=Scientific American|volume=296|issue=4|year=2007|pages=56\u201362|issn=0036-8733|doi=10.1038/scientificamerican0407-56|pmid=17479631|bibcode=2007SciAm.296d..56A}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Maier|first1=Stefan A.|last2=Kik|first2=Pieter G.|last3=Atwater|first3=Harry A.|last4=Meltzer|first4=Sheffer|last5=Harel|first5=Elad|last6=Koel|first6=Bruce E.|last7=Requicha|first7=Ari A.G.|title=Local detection of electromagnetic energy transport below the diffraction limit in metal nanoparticle plasmon waveguides|journal=Nature Materials|volume=2|issue=4|year=2003|pages=229\u2013232|issn=1476-1122|doi=10.1038/nmat852|pmid=12690394|bibcode=2003NatMa...2..229M}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Walters|first1=Robert J.|last2=Bourianoff|first2=George I.|last3=Atwater|first3=Harry A.|title=Field-effect electroluminescence in silicon nanocrystals|journal=Nature Materials|volume=4|issue=2|year=2005|pages=143\u2013146|issn=1476-1122|doi=10.1038/nmat1307|pmid=15665836|bibcode=2005NatMa...4..143W|citeseerx=10.1.1.422.8799}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Lezec|first1=H. J.|last2=Dionne|first2=J. A.|last3=Atwater|first3=H. A.|title=Negative Refraction at Visible Frequencies|journal=Science|volume=316|issue=5823|year=2007|pages=430\u2013432|issn=0036-8075|doi=10.1126/science.1139266|pmid=17379773|bibcode=2007Sci...316..430L|citeseerx=10.1.1.422.9475}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Pacifici|first1=Domenico|last2=Lezec|first2=Henri J.|last3=Atwater|first3=Harry A.|title=All-optical modulation by plasmonic excitation of CdSe quantum dots|journal=Nature Photonics|volume=1|issue=7|year=2007|pages=402\u2013406|issn=1749-4885|doi=10.1038/nphoton.2007.95|bibcode=2007NaPho...1..402P|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/95a575313c61cebee8271fff0283365598316763}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Boltasseva|first1=A.|authorlink1=Alexandra Boltasseva|last2=Atwater|first2=H. A.|title=Low-Loss Plasmonic Metamaterials|journal=Science|volume=331|issue=6015|year=2011|pages=290\u2013291|issn=0036-8075|doi=10.1126/science.1198258|pmid=21252335|bibcode=2011Sci...331..290B}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links/sources ==\n*[http://eas.caltech.edu/people/2917/profile Atwater's profile at Caltech]\n*[http://daedalus.caltech.edu Atwater Research Group Website]\n*[http://www.lmi.caltech.edu Light-Material Interactions in Energy Conversion Energy Frontier Research Center]\n*[http://www.resnick.caltech.edu Resnick Institute]\n*[http://www.eni.com/eni-award/eng/home.shtml ENI Award homepage]\n*[http://spie.org/x112673.xml Harry A. Atwater: SPIE Photonics West plenary presentation: Tunable and Quantum Metaphotonics]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Atwater, Harry}}\n[[Category:Massachusetts Institute of Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:California Institute of Technology faculty]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American physicists]]\n[[Category:American electrical engineers]]\n[[Category:American material